COVERED PATENTS

US Patent Application 63/968,323
  Title:      Methods of and Systems for Distributed Polyglot Function
              Orchestration with Dynamic Runtime Registration and
              Correlated Invocation
  Type:       Provisional Application (35 USC 111(b))
  Filed:      January 26, 2026
  Docket:     MOTIA.003PUS0
  Inventors:  Michael Piccolo, Sergio Marcelino Nobrega de Castro Filho
  Assignee:   Motia LLC
  Status:     Pending

PATENT COVERAGE

The above patent application covers core technologies in III Engine including:

  1. Centralized orchestration engine for distributed function execution
  2. Unified invocation model for local and remote functions
  3. Dynamic runtime registration of functions, triggers, and trigger types
  4. Request-response correlation using unique invocation identifiers
  5. Recursive orchestration (engine-as-worker patterns)
  6. Polyglot function execution across heterogeneous runtimes
  7. Bridge layer protocols for language-agnostic worker participation

